Let's say, as RDS is connected, how does Multi-AZ work internally?

By default RDS is Single AZ.

Default behavior:

Create RDS without Multi-AZ option
→ Single AZ only
→ No standby
→ No automatic failover

You have to explicitly enable it:

AWS Console:

Create RDS after create need to enable
        │
        ▼
Availability & durability section
        │
        ▼
You see two options:
1. Single DB instance      ← default selected
2. Multi-AZ DB instance    ← you must choose this

Cost difference:

Single AZ  → normal price
Multi-AZ   → 2x price
             because two instances running
             primary + standby

Summary:

Enable Multi-AZ → AWS does rest
Sync            → automatic ✅
Failover        → automatic ✅
DNS update      → automatic ✅
Your job        → just enable it ✅
